1.title: LaDorris Résérection
1.plot: Breck, Dainius, Martin and Simone attend the 9th anniversary of LaDorris at Café Cléopatra.

2.title: Fashion Show 2018 Garçons Sculpteurs
2.plot: Breck, Dainius, Simone and Martin attend the 2018 edition of Fashion Garçons Sculpteurs owned by Yanick Daigle and featuring the collection of 5 designers.

3.title: Best of Candyass May 18
3.plot: Breck celebrates his 50th Birthday by attending Best of Candyass May 18 with Martin, Simone and Marie.

4.title: Bagalicious Party Quétaine
4.plot: Breck Stewart and his crew Martin Boulianne, Eric Paradis and Marie Guimond attend the event Bagalicious Party Quétaine hosted by Rita Baga and his guest performers.

5.title: Montreal Fetish Weekend 2018
5.plot: Breck, Simone, Martin, Marie and Dainius attend the 2018 edition of Montreal Fetish Weekend with emcee Yanick Daigle featuring 5 latex designers.

6.title: Black & Blue Chrome
6.plot: Breck, Martin, Dainius and newcomer Donald Deoll attend the 28th edition of Black and Blue Chrome with artistic director Yanick Daigle and the BBCM foundation.

7.title: Carnaval des Couleurs
7.plot: Breck, Martin and Dainius attend the first edition of Carnaval des Couleurs with artistic director Yanick Daigle and the BBCM foundation.

8.title: District Video Lounge 3D
8.plot: Breck, Martin, Simone and Dainius visit Jimmy Moore and his guests at District Video Lounge for the weekly 3D Thursday event.

1.title: Bullying
1.plot: Breck visited the set of a photo shoot to bring to life the concept of Tony Adonis Andrianopoulos. The topic is gay bashing and bullying which in extreme cases can result in murder and suicide.

2.title: Egocentrix
2.plot: Breck meets DJ Egocentrix for an interview on the set of a photo shoot in which he talks about his career in the music business

3.title: Candyass Cabaret
3.plot: We follow Breck backstage at Cleopatra Cafe where he meets the cast and sings one song in the Candyass Cabaret show.

4.title: Blu Nathan
4.plot: Breck meets Blu Nathan, a Yoga teacher and artist who creates electronic world music deeply rooted in spirituality.

5.title: Paul Bergeron
5.plot: Breck Stewart meets Paul Bergeron at G.I. Joe sauna, a fixture in the Montreal gay fetish community as the founder of Dom-ms Academy. He performed S&M shows for more than 40 years in the Montreal club scene.

6.title: Six Sick Sex
6.plot: Breck is on the set of a photo shoot with DJ/Producer Alain Jackinsky for a safe sex campaign originated by Jorge Briceno where they have a frank discussion about the issue.

7.title: Blu Red
7.plot: We follow Breck Stewart as he gets into his "Red" character through a body painting session with singer, songwriter and composer Blu Nathan at Sauna G.I. Joe.

8.title: G.I. Joe 2012
8.plot: Breck hosts a New Year 2012 party at Sauna G.I. Joe with the countdown to midnight shot live on December 31st, 2011.

9.title: P.P.P. Party
9.plot: We follow Breck Stewart backstage as he prepares to perform at the P.P.P. Party hosted by Daniel Duhamel in the same location where Breck's fourth single from Mister E "Disturbing Bliss" was recorded.

10.title: G.I. Valentine
10.plot: We follow Breck in a body painting session at G.I. Joe sauna shot on Valentine's Day 2012. The video features the new outside window display of G.I. Joe inaugurated on March 11, 2012. Four of the six models in the window display are in the video including Breck, Jorge Briceno, Bruno Leto and Claude Guerin.

11.title: D-Siren
11.plot: Breck Stewart meets DJ D-Siren with his sidekick Laure Paulus at Complexe Sky on Ste-Catherine Street in Montreal on White Party Week-End 2012 edition.

12.title: Cantelli as Whitney Houston
12.plot: Breck Stewart performs as "George Michael" with female impersonator and singer Cantelli De Ramos as "Whitney Houston" at Cabaret Mado.

13.title: Making of Exotic Celebration
13.plot: This is the making of Exotic Celebration, the fifth single of Mister E album by Breck Stewart with music and mastering by 604-ToKay (Hans Kremer). Breck plays King Zertivio and the video also features Kymara Kia Lee as Empress Mialona and Daniele Ducharme as Countess Expressia with clothes by designer Sandra Claros who also makes an appearance.

14.title: Making of Razor Laugh
14.plot: Making of Razor Laugh, the 6th single of Mister E album by Breck Stewart, original music by Jim Robson. Breck plays King Zertivio and the video also features Kymara Kia Lee as Empress Mialona, recorded at Complexe Sky.

15.title: Cantelli on the Go
15.plot: Breck visits Cantelli who performs at Le Cabaret with his team of dancers.

16.title: Trio Does Cantelli Chez Mado
16.plot: Breck follows guest star singer/drag queen Cantelli De Ramos who is preparing to perform at Cabaret Chez Mado and Complexe Sky with cameos by Tante Gaby and Madame Simone.

17.title: 25 Years NA Celebration
17.plot: Psychotherapist, social worker, caterer and painter Marcalain Marticotte celebrates his 25 years of abstinence from alcohol, drugs, gambling and medication. Proud member of Narcotics Anonymous, he helps others find their way towards recovery. For this special occasion, he receives his family from Gaspesie, his friends and many members of Narcotics Anonymous.

18.title: Candyass Redneck Cabaret
18.plot: Breck, Marcalain and Jacob visit Candyass Cabaret "Redneck" edition with the troupe of Velma Candyass and guests including Nat King Pole, Diane Labelle, Lisa Maria Diano, Marianne Trenka, Roxie Hardon, Punani Difranco, Damiana Dolce, Jimmy Phul (Jason McCullough), Corey T, Gillian Richards, Bonnie Scott, Tenyjah Mckenna, Elise Ebner, Genie Emerald and Hugo Trottier.

19.title: Denis & Marie-Noelle
19.plot: We witness the wedding of Denis Fortin and Marie-Noelle Langlais in the Gaspe Peninsula while Breck and Marcalain do a photo shoot with MoonDaze Productions.

20.title: Drugstore & Mascara
20.plot: Breck visits LaDorris for her show at Drugstore and he also goes with Marcalain backstage at Mascara 2013 in the Old-Port in Montreal. Patricia La Coquine and Gonzito Boubou from The Tikiboum Clan fight with Mangoo the cat.

21.title: Galaxy Guide
21.plot: Breck as alien Ritovak visits the Candyass Cabaret show with Velma Candyass and her troupe including Nat King Pole, Diane Labelle, Marianne Trenka, Roxie Hardon, Punani Difranco, Damiana Dolce, Jimmy Phule, Bonnie Scott, Jolie Seraphina, La Cherie Coquette, Andrea Patricia Sierra (Lolita Blanca), Caroline Kamar (Chibbi Tea), Jeannie Goodwitch, Lulu Les Belles Mirettes, Mademoizella A. Choregraphe, Richard Erno and photographer Hugo Trottier.

22.title: Rejeanne & St-James Gala
22.plot: It's about two events: the departure of Rejeanne Marticotte from Montreal to her native Gaspesie where she will move in with with her parents to take care of them and a fundraiser at the McGill Faculty Club for the St-James Drop-In Centre which is an organization to help the homeless, people with drug addictions and/or mental issues and also offers them a way to express themselves through an art program. Also featuring Martin Boulianne, Simone SilverLining, Bernard Racicot, Lysanne Picard, Marcalain Marticotte, Nicole Marticotte, Sonia Marticotte, Laval Coulombe, ...

23.title: Marcalain & Melissa
23.plot: Holiday Special 2013 where Breck attends the opening of the new painting collection by Marcalain Marticotte and Melissa Di Lauro at Studio Backstage. Introducing three new Tikiboum Clan characters Drakonito Kishta, Zerpilou Tesso and Larry the 6th voices supplied by Breck Stewart.

1.title: Quebec Canada
1.plot: MoonDaze TV 24 is the first episode of season 02. Breck as character "QueCan" attends the Candyass Club Cabaret show about The Quebec and Canada culture featuring Velma Candyass and her troupe. Meanwhile, Quebec Princess Patricia La Coquine and Queen of Canada Coccinella from The Tikiboum Clan fight over who is the ultimate monarch.

2.title: Russian Gay Love
2.plot: MoonDaze TV 25 is the second episode of season 02 and a Valentine Day Special with Breck, Marcalain, Mangoo and the Tikiboum Clan. Breck performs as Vladimir Schovak with Velma and her troupe at Candyass Cabaret in a show about Russia called Midnight in Moscow. Meanwhile, The Grim Sisters try to upstage the Tikiboum Clan (vocals by Breck Stewart).

3.title: David & Marcel
3.plot: MoonDaze TV 26 is the third episode of season 02 with Breck, Marcalain, Mangoo and the Tikiboum Clan. Breck meets Davyn Ryall, the author and producer of the play David starring Stevy Turmel in a one man show using video sequences to enhance the story featuring Breck as David. We also surprise Marcel Cliche with a special Meritas award and celebrate Laval Coulombe for his birthday.

4.title: Ready for the 80's
4.plot: MoonDaze TV 27 is the fourth episode of season 02 starring Breck Stewart with Simone Silverlining and the Tikiboum Clan (vocals by Breck Stewart). Breck performs as Robert Palmer and Amadeus with Velma Candyass and her troupe at Candyass Cabaret in a show about the 1980's with MC Ryan Graham Hinds.

5.title: Lady Hoops in the City
5.plot: MoonDaze TV 28 is the fifth episode of season 02 starring Breck Stewart. He follows Marianne Trenka as Lady Hoops in 2 events including the 11th "Nuit Blanche" (White Night) in Montreal and An Evening in Paris organized by Lady and Kelli Hanrahan who form the duo act Hulala as part of HoopDanse.

6.title: Nuits de Montréal
6.plot: MoonDaze TV 29 is the sixth episode of season 02 starring Breck Stewart. Breck performs as Harry & Tim with Pyro Metheus, Velma Candyass and her troupe at Candyass Cabaret in a show that pokes fun at the construction scandal in Quebec known as "Commission Charbonneau".

7.title: LaDorris 5 ans
7.plot: MoonDaze TV 30 is the seventh episode of season 02 starring Breck Stewart with special guest star LaDorris who celebrates his 5 Year Anniversary in the Drag Queen world at Apollon with host Barbada featuring Jimmy Moore, Michel Dorion, Penelope, Rainbow Vyxen, Chou Choune, Paradox Xodorap. Certain segments are in French.

8.title: Gold Dreams
8.plot: MoonDazeTV 31 is the 8th episode of season 02 starring Breck Stewart. Breck goes to The Wiggle Room for the first time to support his friends Martin Giroux known as The Stretcher (also featured in the soundtrack as DigitalMindWarp), Natasha Nebula with the Black Snake Circus and magician Jonathan Gold with MC Kitty Vanderbuilt (Lise Vigneault). Also featuring Marianne Trenka as Lady Hoops and Sacha Cloutier.

9.title: Chic Choc Montréal
9.plot: MoonDaze TV 32 is the 9th episode of season 02 starring Breck Stewart. Breck attends the Chic Choc Montréal event held at Musée De Cire Grévin located in Centre Eaton organized by André-Léonard Nantel who is the founder of the project to create a permanent set of shows. Also featuring Olivier Martias, Jessy Gauthier, François Gagnon, Martin Boulianne, Martin Giroux, Patricia Demers, Mireille Enjoie, Stanley Norris, Marianne Trenka, Kelli Hanrahan, Cantelli, Julia Sacchetto, Arianne La Salle, Stéphanie Cloutier, Eavee Love, William-Maxime Fortin, Marcelle Aubin-Messier...

10.title: Fringe Festival
10.plot: MoonDaze TV 33 is the 10th episode of season 02 starring Breck Stewart. Breck covers 2 Fringe Festival events including the play David adapted by Davyn Ryall with Stevy Turmel who is the solo performer and the show called Turning Tricks by Glam Gam Productions at Café Cleopatra. Also featuring The Stretcher (Martin Giroux), Michael J McCarthy, Phoenix Wood, Misty Portugal, Hannah Morrow, Kay Pee, Julie Paquet, Roscoe Stone, Micheline Chartier, Sky Stryker, Jessica Klein, Tanya Stasilowitch, Seth Scheuner, Sam Sullivan, Tristan Ginger, Booze Crotch, Erik Mockus, ...

11.title: Première
11.plot: MoonDaze TV 34 is the 11th episode of season 02 starring Breck Stewart. We see the 4 month process of preparing a painting exhibition at Lallouz Ste-Catherine and Studio Backstage with Marcalain Marticotte as art teacher and his students Genevieve Benjamin, Guy Bourgeois, Minou Labonte, Paola Fragasso and Marie-Hélène Hébert. Some sequences are in French.

12.title: Making of 2 Is the Norm
12.plot: MoonDaze TV 35 is the 12th episode of season 02. Behind the scenes look on the making of Single 8 of Mister E album "2 is the Norm" by Breck Stewart, music and mastering by 604-ToKay (Hans Kremer). Breck plays King Zertivio and the video also features Kymara Kia Lee as Empress Mialona, Holy Scar, Art Mtz, Jyps Despins and Carlos Carnegato. The soundtrack includes the music of SteVan Horne, DigitalMindWarp, Fafnirrockson and Myles Marriott. Camera 1 by Sacha Cloutier and Breck, camera 2 by Martin Boulianne and Carlos Carnegato.

13.title: Change
13.plot: MoonDaze TV 36 is the 13th and last episode of season 02. Breck Stewart summons Van Hechter to a facial hair duel involving shaving and banter, featuring the song Danceterium by guest star/singer Van formerly of the Where's Mickey band in his first foray into a solo career. Also featuring Martin Boulianne, Simone SilverLining and Sacha Cloutier.

1.title: Spacey Nineties
1.plot: MoonDaze TV 37 is the first episode of season 03 starring Breck Stewart. Breck and his team at MoonDaze Productions go behind the scenes of the new Candyass Cabaret show "Spacey Nineties". Featuring Velma Candyass, Tranna Wintour, Ryan Graham Hinds, Nat King Pole, Empress of Squee, Chibbi Tea, DJ Franco, Clare Ann Higgins, Velvet La Touche, Martin Giroux as The Stretcher, Diane Labelle, Pyro Metheus, Aurora Boreali. Music by Fafnirrockson, SteVan Horne, DigitalMindWarp, Myles Marriott and MikeWhitePresents.

2.title: Santa Barbada
2.plot: MoonDaze TV 38 is the second episode of season 03 starring Breck Stewart. Breck and his team at MoonDaze Productions (Simone SilverLining, Martin Boulianne, Marie Guimond) go behind the scenes at Cabaret Mado to attend a fundraiser hosted by Emcee drag queen Barbada de Barbades (David Potvin). Featuring Phoenix Vyxen, Heaven G., Peggy Sue, Rainbow Drag, music by Fafnirrockson, SteVan Horne, bigfix, Myles Marriott and Primo1. Half English, Moitié Français.

3.title: (in)Famous Women
3.plot: MoonDaze TV 39 is the third episode of season 03 starring Breck Stewart. Breck and his MoonDaze Productions team go behind the scenes of the 37th Candyass Cabaret show "(in)Famous Women". Soundtrack music by Fafnirrockson, SteVan Horne, Myles Marriott and Primo1 with excerpts of original live songs by Leighland Beckman, Nat King Pole, Damiana Dolce and Jeannie Goodwitch. Contains live performances by Velma Candyass, Diane Labelle, Maxine Segalowitz, Dawn Ford, Kitty DeMure, Empress of Squee with MC Tranna Wintour also featuring DJ Franco, Chibbi Tea, Emily Brown and ...

4.title: Dare Moore
4.plot: MoonDaze TV 40 is the fourth episode of season 03 starring Breck Stewart. Breck, Martin Boulianne, Simone SilverLining and Marie Guimond go behind the scenes at Cabaret Mado to see Jimmy Moore who celebrates 15 years of Madonna impersonation. Music by Fafnirrockson, SteVan Horne, Myles Marriott, MikeWhitePresents and Primo1.

5.title: Chastity Ball
5.plot: MoonDazeTV 41 is the fifth episode of season 03 starring Breck Stewart. Breck and his MoonDaze Productions team go behind the scenes of the 39th Candyass Cabaret show "Chastity Ball". Soundtrack music by DigitalMindWarp, Fafnirrockson, SteVan Horne, Myles Marriott and Primo1. Featuring Velma Candyass, James Douglas, Bonnie Scott, Arabella Alure, Honey Fury, DJ Franco, Chibbi Tea, Swagg'r Lee, Paco (Pacolita), Lili Pop, Diane Labelle, Nat King Pole, Leighland Beckman, Jeannie Goodwitch, Damiana Dolce, Empress of Squee, Emily Brown, Kathy Slamen (Miss Kaliope), Velvet ...

6.title: Dorion Making Up
6.plot: MoonDazeTV 42 is the sixth episode of season 03 with Breck Stewart featuring singer and drag queen Michel Dorion who released his first song and video clip "Making up (Une seule vie)". The original song is produced by Michel and directed, written and composed by Frederic Luc. The episode contains excerpts of the original video clip produced, assembled, directed and edited by Jihef Portelance and features dancers Marc-André Caron (also choreographer), Jean-Marc Reid, Nikkie Lafontaine and Marco Boudreau. It also contains behind the scenes tidbits and performances by ...

7.title: Exposition Illusions
7.plot: MoonDazeTV 43 is the 7th episode of season 03 with Breck Stewart who visits the Galerie Dentaire on Amherst street which is a dentist office with an art gallery. Marie-Josée Gagnon is the artist featured and Breck also talks with manager Elody Bachoffner who takes him on a tour of the establishment. Soundtrack music composers and songs include SteVan Horne "Where Does it Go", Fafnirrockson "Chefsache" (MoonDaze TV theme) and "Opferanode", Myles Marriott "Don't Look Back", DigitalMindWarp "Groove" and Primo1 "FlowingSynergy". The episode is half in French and half in ...

8.title: Deep in the Bush
8.plot: MoonDazeTV 44 is the 8th episode of season 03 starring Breck Stewart. Breck and his MoonDaze Productions team go behind the scenes of the 40th Candyass Cabaret show "Deep in the Bush". Soundtrack music by SteVan Horne, Myles Marriott, Fafnirrockson and Primo1 with live singing performances by Leighland Beckman, Nat King Pole, Damiana Dolce and Eavee Love.

9.title: Making of Sun Rays
9.plot: MoonDazeTV 45 is the 9th episode of season 03 about the making of the music video for the song Sun Rays by Breck Stewart. Music and mastering by Fafnirrockson with lyrics and vocals by Breck who also directed and edited the video produced by MoonDaze Productions. Featuring Richard Erno as Pyro Metheus, Nicole Heaslewood and Mirabelle Charette.

10.title: LaDorris Carte Blanche
10.plot: MoonDazeTV 46 is the 10th and finale episode of season 03 with Breck Stewart. Drag Queen Luc "LaDorris" Baillargeon stars in a show called Carte Blanche recorded at Bar Le Cocktail in Montreal featuring Barbada, Styla and Bibeau Gab with cameo by Olivier Tremblay. Soundtrack composers include SteVan Horne, DigitalMindWarp, Myles Marriott, Fafnirrockson and Primo1. Half English, Moitié Français.

1.title: Cléo 5 à 7
1.plot: MoonDazeTV 47 is the first episode of season 04 with Breck Stewart. Breck and his MoonDaze Productions team go behind the scenes at the Candyass Cabaret show "Cléo 5 à 7". Soundtrack music by SteVan Horne, Myles Marriott, Fafnirrockson and Primo1 with live singing performances by Nat King Pole, Damiana Dolce, Jeannie Goodwitch and Ghostly Hounds.

2.title: Le Milieu
2.plot: MoonDazeTV 48 is the second episode of season 04. Breck Stewart and Simone SilverLining reflect on the world economy as they also visit Le Milieu, a volunteer based cooperative where people with low means can produce art such as crafts, knitting, painting etc. Soundtrack music by SteVan Horne, Alain Jacob, Myles Marriott, Fafnirrockson and Primo1.

3.title: Le GenderSwitch Show
3.plot: MoonDazeTV 49 is the third episode of season 04 with Breck Stewart. Breck as "Breckinette" and his MoonDaze Productions team go behind the scenes of the 45th Candyass Cabaret "Le GenderSwitch Show". Soundtrack music by SteVan Horne, Alain Jacob, Falik, Fafnirrockson and Primo1 with live singing performances by Nat King Pole, Damiana Dolce, Leighland Beckman and Cameron Eric Leon.

4.title: Pompette
4.plot: MoonDazeTV 50 is the fourth episode of season 04. Breck Stewart as CandyDude and his MoonDaze Productions team including Simone SilverLining, Martin Boulianne and Marie Guimond go behind the scenes of the show Pompette hosted by LaDorris (Luc Baillargeon) who celebrates 7 years of drag queen performances at Café Cléopatra where it all began. Moitié Français, Half English.

5.title: Country Tyme
5.plot: MoonDaze TV 51 is the fifth episode of season 04 where we celebrate Breck Stewart and Simone SilverLining's Birthday at the 47th edition of Candyass Cabaret "Country Tyme". Soundtrack music by Fafnirrockson "Chefsache", SteVan Horne "Pope Idol", Alain Jacob "Sensuelle Sensation", DigitalMindWarp (Martin Giroux) "Funky", MylesMarriott "Tranceatlantic" and Primo1 "Santa Sense" with live performances by Damiana Dolce, Nat King Pole and Caribou Stew "Will The Circle Be Unbroken".

6.title: Piqot's Art
6.plot: MoonDaze TV 52 is the sixth episode of season 04 where Breck, Simone, Martin and Marie meet artist Jacques Aleksandre Piqot at Van Houtte Cafe and also visit his painting studio at home. Soundtrack music includes SteVan Horne "Island of the Deadbeat", Alain Jacob "Retour aux Sources", Myles Marriott "Freedom", Fafnirrockson "Hot_L(Espresso Mix)" and Primo1 "Digging Free". Some sequences are in French with no subtitles. Cast: Breck Stewart, Jaques Aleksandre Piqot, Simone SilverLining, Martin Boulianne, Marie Guimond.

7.title: Montreal Fetish Weekend 2016
7.plot: Breck attends the 12th edition of Montreal Fetish Weekend on Labor Day Weekend 2016 and wears the clothes of 2 designers Il Bolero and Exxess Latex. Featuring 147 different personalities behind the scenes and in front of the camera.

8.title: MFW Fashions
8.plot: Breck, Martin, Simone, Marie and Candace visit John Sardelli the owner of fetish clothing store Il Bolero at Plaza St-Hubert celebrating its 25 year anniversary. The video also includes runway segments and behind the scenes footage recorded at Café Cléopâtre, Garçons Sculpteurs & Club Unity during Montreal Fetish Weekend 2016 featuring the clothes and accessories of 8 designers with many models and personalities in front of the camera and behind the scenes.

9.title: Black & Blue Stardust
9.plot: Breck, Kathy and Martin celebrate the 5th Anniversary of MoonDaze TV by attending the 26th edition of Black & Blue Stardust with artistic director Yanick Daigle and the BBCM foundation featuring 70+ artists.

10.title: Shimmies & Showtunes
10.plot: Breck Stewart, Simone SilverLining, Martin Boulianne & Kathy Slamen celebrate the 50th show of Candyass Cabaret with Velma Candyass and her troupe.

1.title: Holiday Feast
1.plot: Breck, Kathy and Martin attend the 51st Candyass Cabaret show to celebrate the 2016 Holiday Season at Café Cléopatra.

2.title: Jason's Mission
2.plot: Breck, Simone, Martin and Marie pay a visit to Jason Noël the founder of LGBT in the city to discuss his mission in the Montreal community. Includes French segments taken from LGBT in the city videos. Half English. Moitié Français.

3.title: LaDorris Last Call
3.plot: Breck is invited by LaDorris (Luc Baillargeon) who is retiring from drag performances to attend a last show Last Call. Simone, Marie and Martin as the crew also join the fun and we get introduced to several new characters.

4.title: Fashion Show Garçons Sculpteurs 2017
4.plot: Breck, Velma, Simone and Martin visit Le 281 to attend the event Fashion Show Garçons Sculpteurs 2017 which represents the artistic vision of Yanick Daigle with 50+ artists including fashion designers, models, dancers and performers. Half English - Moitié Français.

5.title: Fashion Show Yanick Daigle 2017
5.plot: Breck Stewart and Martin Boulianne visit the camping site "Domaine de la Fierté" in Ste-Julienne to record the annual fashion show of Yanick Daigle with 5 designers and 15 models also featuring 5 composers of electronic dance music with behind the scenes exclusives. Half English - Moitié Français.

6.title: House of Laureen Pride Edition
6.plot: Breck meets Connie Lingua the mother of House of Laureen that includes 5 other members as a family unit at their Pride Edition show featuring many guests celebrating for LGBTQ rights at Café Cléopatra.

7.title: Montreal Fetish Weekend 2017
7.plot: Breck, Martin, Simone and Jubeleela Bing-Bing attend the 13th edition of Montreal Fetish Weekend with stylist and Garçons Sculpteurs owner Yanick Daigle, fetish clothing designers Il Bolero, Patrice Catanzaro, Cheeky Latex, Exxess Latex, Phoenix Latex, Kustom Latex Designs and their models walking the red carpet.

8.title: Black & Blue Luminocity
8.plot: Breck, Velma and Simon go to the 27th edition of Black and Blue in a show called Luminocity by artistic director Yanick Daigle featuring his troupe of performers.

9.title: Red Christmas
9.plot: Breck, Simone, Shehrazade and Dainius attend the 60th edition of Candyass Cabaret Holiday Special "Red Christmas" including bloopers and outtakes.

imdb.title: MoonDaze TV
plot: Follow Breck Stewart's nightlife in Montreal featuring artists, performers, friends, fans, guests and various people he meets along the way. The crew is visible and part of the cast. Half English. Moitié Français.::MoonDaze Productions
